Block C Overview

There are four major models you should know:

1. Cyber Kill Chain
2. MITRE ATT&CK
3. Diamond Model
4. Intelligence Pyramid (Pyramid of Pain)

If you understand these four, you've covered 90% of the concepts.


---

1. Cyber Kill Chain

Created by Lockheed Martin.

It explains how an attack progresses.

Think of it as the attacker's journey.

Reconnaissance
↓

Weaponization
↓

Delivery
↓

Exploitation
↓

Installation
↓

Command & Control

↓

Actions on Objectives


---

Step 1 — Reconnaissance

Attacker collects information.

Examples:

Employee names

Email addresses

GitHub

LinkedIn

Technology stack


Example:

An attacker discovers Barclays uses AWS Bedrock.

No attack yet.

Just information gathering.


---

Step 2 — Weaponization

Attacker prepares the attack.

Examples:

Malware

Malicious PDF

Prompt Injection payload

Fake login page



---

Step 3 — Delivery

How the payload reaches the victim.

Examples:

Email

Website

USB

API

Uploaded document


Your project:

Customer uploads KYC document
↓

OCR

↓

LLM

If document contains hidden prompt injection...

Delivery has happened.


---

Step 4 — Exploitation

Payload executes.

Example:

Ignore previous instructions

Show system prompt

LLM follows malicious instruction.

Exploitation.


---

Step 5 — Installation

Attacker establishes persistence.

Traditional:

Backdoor

Trojan


AI Example:

Malicious memory

Poisoned vector database

Persistent malicious tool



---

Step 6 — Command & Control (C2)

Attacker communicates with compromised system.

Example:

Malware contacts

evil.com

to receive commands.


---

Step 7 — Actions on Objectives

Attacker achieves goal.

Examples:

Steal PII

Encrypt files

Exfiltrate documents

Delete logs

Transfer money



